    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-06T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-06T12:00:00-05:00" n="815"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d815">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1102</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-06T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 7, 6.50 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1519. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1"
                        >Chadbourne</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 142. Your 132. Concerning [plan that] vessels not touching American ports
                    proceeding from South American ports, etc., be compelled to call Porto Rico,
                    etc. Before attempting to arrange do you insist on including South America east
                    ports? Reason for asking is the extent of deviation of ships from east coast.
                    Rumored here Spain attempting arrangements to import cotton proceeding from
                    Torreon district in Mexico. If it is true, may have connection with the assembly
                    of coal at Tampico to obtain evasion of our jurisdiction.
                        <persName>Smith</persName>. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1"
                        >Chadbourne</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
